('computer-science:2-2-3d-sql:exam:3086a0ad', 'computer-science', 'computer-science:2-2-3d-sql', '2.2.3d SQL', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q1", "question": "<p>The table below shows a school football club, <strong>Squad</strong>.</p><pre>PlayerID | Name   | Position   | Age | Goals\n1        | Alex   | Striker    | 17  | 12\n2        | Priya  | Midfielder | 15  | 5\n3        | Sam    | Defender   | 16  | 1\n4        | Jordan | Striker    | 14  | 8\n5        | Kim    | Midfielder | 17  | 3\n6        | Reo    | Defender   | 15  | 0</pre><p>Tick <strong>one</strong> box to identify what  SELECT * FROM Squad  returns.</p>", "options": ["All 5 fields, for all 6 players", "Only the Name field, for all 6 players", "All 5 fields, but only for Alex, the first player in the table", "Nothing, because a SELECT statement must always include a WHERE clause to run at all"], "hint": "* means ''every field''. With no WHERE clause, every row is also returned."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\">\n<h5>Mark Scheme — 1 mark</h5>\n<ul><li><strong>All 5 fields, for all 6 players</strong></li></ul>\n</div>", "modelAnswer": "All 5 fields, for all 6 players."}'::jsonb),
('computer-science:2-2-3d-sql:exam:724f7d51', 'computer-science', 'computer-science:2-2-3d-sql', '2.2.3d SQL', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q2", "question": "<p>Tick <strong>one</strong> box to identify which SQL keyword filters which ROWS a query returns.</p>", "options": ["WHERE", "SELECT", "FROM", "AND, since this is the only keyword that is ever able to filter which rows come back from a query"], "hint": "SELECT picks fields (columns). FROM names the table. Which keyword is left to filter rows?"}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\">\n<h5>Mark Scheme — 1 mark</h5>\n<ul><li><strong>WHERE</strong></li></ul>\n</div>", "modelAnswer": "WHERE."}'::jsonb),
